<headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 16 at 1:05AM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of Pittsburg County
through 145 AM CDT...
At 105 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from 4 miles northwest of Scipio to 5 miles west of
Ashland to near Centrahoma. Movement was southeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 45 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects.
Locations in or near the path include...
Mcalester...                      Hartshorne...
Krebs...                          Kiowa...
Savanna...                        Alderson...
Ashland...                        Haywood...
Mcalester Regional Airport...     Scipio...
Blanco...                         Haileyville...
Pittsburg...                      Arpelar...
Dow...                            Bache...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
